ubdivide the sample by galactocentric radius, we find that the age\ndistributions remain unchanged. However, the mass spectral index varies\nsignificantly, showing best fit values between $-2.2$ and $-1.8$, with the\nshallower slope in the highest star formation intensity regions. We explore the\nrobustness of our study to potential systematics and conclude that the cluster\nmass function may vary with respect to environment.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Thu, 27 Feb 2014 19:49:18 GMT"}],"update_date":"2015-06-18"}
